<p><br>Dear teacher,<br><br>In two weeks an Ans inspection for @{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Vaktitel']} (@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['Vakcode']}) will take place.<br><br><strong>What can I expect?</strong><br>Just like during the exam Assistant Floor Managers (AFM'ers) will be present on location. They will tend to the technical aspect of the inspection, while you're expected to take care of the content of the inspection. The inspection is protected with a password, which the AFM'er will share with the students when you're ready to start the inspection. After logging in, students will see the exam questions, their answers and the points they've been awarded. <br><br><strong>How do I prepare for the inspection?</strong><br>The timeslot during which the inspection will be available has been configured according to the timetable, so you will not have to configure this. If you wish for students to see other information than described above, you can adjust the inspection settings yourself as described on <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/45162/pages/tools-ans-inspection">this page</a>. If you are pleased with the settings, you do not have to take any further action.<br><br><strong>About the inspection:</strong></p>
